      • matches

        public StringAssertion matches(String pattern,
                               String... patternDescArg)
        Verifies that a string matches some pattern.

        Uses java.util.regex.Matcher.find() which means pattern doesn't have to match whole string.

        Parameters:
        pattern - a regular expression representing the pattern to match (e.g. "foo" or "\s+hello\s+")
        patternDescArg - an optional description of the pattern
        Returns:
        this if the string matches the pattern
        Throws:
        AssertionError - if the string does not match the pattern
        PatternSyntaxException - if the pattern does not compile
